      astronomer Phidias. He was friends with King Hieron II, and later with his son Gelon. A.
      probably spent some time in Alexandria; he later sent on his writings to the mathematicians
      (Conon, Dositheus, Eratosthenes) who were working there. In Syracuse, A. studied problems of
